# Summary

You need to reload packages (and data) in every chapter, unlike in our previous Bookdown setups.

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
library(pacman)
p_load(downlit)

devtools::install_github("rethinkpriorities/rp-r-package")
library(rethinkpriorities)

devtools::install_github("rethinkpriorities/r-noodling-package")
library(rnoodling)
```
:::

## Air Quality {#air-quality}

@fig-airquality further explores the impact of temperature on ozone level.

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
library(pacman)
p_load(ggplot2)
library(ggplot2)

ggplot(airquality, aes(Temp, Ozone)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method = "loess"
)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![Temperature and ozone level.](summary_files/figure-html/fig-airquality-1.png){#fig-airquality width=672}
:::
